section.section.services-section#services
  .container
    .row
      .col-lg-6
        .section-title
          h2 Things you should know...
          p Following is some short information which would help you in understanding this calculator module more easily.
    .row
      //  feaure box 
      .col-sm-6.col-lg-4
        .feature-box-1
          //- .icon
          img(src="../images/topic1.png", alt="topics")
          .feature-content
            h5 Soil NPK
            p The soil NPK is the amount of NPK(Nitrogen,Phosphorus,Potassium) in your land. It can be measured in kg/acre. You can get this information from soil testers. This information is important to generate our results. Even if you don't know your soilNPK then you can get this info via our web.  
      //  / 
      //  feaure box 
      .col-sm-6.col-lg-4
        .feature-box-1
          img(src="../images/topic2.png", alt="topics")
          .feature-content
            h5 Fertilizer NPK
            p The NPK values which are printed on any fertilizer packet you buy, is what we mean fertilizer NPK. It is the ratio of NPK(Nitrogen,Phosphorus,Potassium) present in fertilizer. You can get this from the lable of fertilizer you'll buy. It is important to know for our calculator to generate results.
      //  / 
      //  feaure box 
      .col-sm-6.col-lg-4
        .feature-box-1
          img(src="../images/topic3.png", alt="topics")
          .feature-content
            h5 More accuracy, more better results
            p This calculator is able to give you the information about the fertilizer amount, NPK kg per acre amd much more, this information can save your time and provide much accurate results which may help you to grow your crops with more efficiency.
      //  feaure box 
      .col-sm-6.col-lg-4
        .feature-box-1
          img(src="../images/topic4.png", alt="topics")
          .feature-content
            h5 So what is NPK actually?
            p Well NPK means Nitrogen, Phosphorus and Potassium, these are nutrients. These are some most important ingredients in most of fertilizers. These nutrients are required by plants and crops to grow. In ever fertilizer their is different ratio of NPK.
      //  / 
      //  feaure box 
      .col-sm-6.col-lg-4
        .feature-box-1
          img(src="../images/topic5.png", alt="topics")
          .feature-content
            h5 Where to know NPK levels?
            p You can get the current level of NPK value in your farm with the help of our website. Our website can also provide you the contacts, addresses, mobile number and locations of well know soil tester from where you can get this info.
      //  / 
      //  feaure box 
      .col-sm-6.col-lg-4
        .feature-box-1
          img(src="../images/topic6.png", alt="topics")
          .feature-content
            h5 Errors and accuracy
            p This fertilizer-calculator is able to give almost accurate results, but at very end it's still made by humans. Sometimes it may generate inaccurate or incorrect results. The amount of fertilizer changes on may factors which cannot be measured on wensite only so this can cause inaccuracy in results.
      //  / 
